OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F447A1774037478
OL,3,CMurder trial told evidence points to
OL,4,C'some other killer'
OL,6,FThe evidence in the trial of a man
OL,7,Faccused of murdering Natalie McNally
OL,8,Fpoints towards "some other killer", a
OL,9,Fjury has been told by the defence.
OL,11,FDelivering his closing submissions at
OL,12,FBelfast Crown Court, defence barrister
OL,13,FJohn Kearney KC said the case against
OL,14,FStephen McCullagh is "dependent upon
OL,15,Fcircumstantial evidence".
OL,17,FMs McNally, 32, was 15 weeks' pregnant
OL,18,Fwhen she was beaten and stabbed at her
OL,19,Fhome in Lurgan on December 18 2022.
OL,26,@pD@POUpD@bO]vD@VOUwD@XO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G1/13
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,448,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44702
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F447A1774037478
OL,3,CMurder trial told evidence points to
OL,4,C'some other killer'
OL,6,FHer partner, Stephen McCullagh, 36, of
OL,7,FWoodland Gardens in Lisburn, is on
OL,8,Ftrial accused of murdering her.
OL,10,FHe has denied the charge.
OL,12,FThe jury of six men and six women was
OL,13,Ftold on Thursday they would have to
OL,14,Fdecide their verdict on all of the
OL,15,Fevidence in the case.
OL,17,FMr Kearney said the "devil is in the
OL,18,Fdetail" of the evidence.
OL,26,@yD@UOUzD@GO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G2/13
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,448,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44703
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F447A1774037478
OL,3,CMurder trial told evidence points to
OL,4,C'some other killer'
OL,6,FHe said: "There are some inconvenient,
OL,7,Ftroubling, nagging, not unreasonable
OL,8,Fdoubt pieces that do not fit the
OL,9,Fprosecution case.
OL,11,F"There are multiple pieces of this
OL,12,Fcircumstantial jigsaw that point not
OL,13,Ftowards the defendant, but we would
OL,14,Fsuggest point away from him towards
OL,15,Fsome other killer."
OL,17,FHe added: "We ask you to scratch the
OL,18,Fsurface from the superficial points to
OL,19,Fthose matters we suggest will be
OL,20,Fniggling and nagging reasonable doubts
OL,21,Fin this case."
OL,26,@nD@JOUsD@AOUwD@SO]yD@KOU}D@NO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G3/13
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,448,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44704
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F447A1774037478
OL,3,CMurder trial told evidence points to
OL,4,C'some other killer'
OL,6,FMr Kearney said the defendant was
OL,7,Fentitled to the presumption of
OL,8,Finnocence.
OL,10,FHe added that McCullagh had not given
OL,11,Fevidence during the trial and the jury
OL,12,Fdid not have to "hold that against"
OL,13,Fhim.
OL,15,FHe said the jury was also entitled to
OL,16,Ftake into account the "state of the
OL,17,Fevidence" against the defendant.
OL,19,FThe barrister said the failure of
OL,20,FMcCullagh to give evidence "doesn't
OL,21,Fmake an unproven case proven".
OL,26,@tD@QOUtD@cO]xD@WOUyD@IO]|D@\OU}D@]O]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G4/13
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,448,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44705
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F447A1774037478
OL,3,CMurder trial told evidence points to
OL,4,C'some other killer'
OL,6,FHe added: "It doesn't get the
OL,7,Fprosecution to their end line on its
OL,8,Fown."
OL,10,FMr Kearney said it was a "classic
OL,11,Fcircumstantial case, dependent upon
OL,12,Fcircumstantial evidence".
OL,14,FHe said there is no eyewitness
OL,15,Fevidence and there was only Ms McNally
OL,16,Fand her killer in the house on the
OL,17,Fnight she was murdered.
OL,26,@nD@KOUpD@EO]rD@ZOUtD@XO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G5/13
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,448,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44706
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F447A1774037478
OL,3,CMurder trial told evidence points to
OL,4,C'some other killer'
OL,6,FThe barrister said the jury had to
OL,7,Fhave no reasonable doubt that
OL,8,FMcCullagh was the killer before they
OL,9,Fcould convict.
OL,11,FHe said: "When you come to this
OL,12,Fcritically important decision on the
OL,13,Fidentity of the killer, if you think
OL,14,Fhe probably is the killer: not enough.
OL,15,FIf you are almost sure he is the
OL,16,Fkiller: not enough.
OL,18,F"If you are left with a reasonable
OL,19,Fdoubt that someone else could have
OL,20,Fbeen the killer your job is to acquit."
OL,26,@sD@JOUzD@AOU|D@gO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G6/13
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,448,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44707
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F447A1774037478
OL,3,CMurder trial told evidence points to
OL,4,C'some other killer'
OL,6,FMr Kearney turned to CCTV evidence
OL,7,Fpresented by the prosecution.
OL,9,FHe said a "big problem" for the
OL,10,Fprosecution was the absence of CCTV
OL,11,Fshowing McCullagh leaving his house in
OL,12,FLisburn on the night Ms McNally was
OL,13,Fkilled.
OL,15,FHe said: "If the prosecution case is
OL,16,Fright, he should have been picked up
OL,17,Fleaving his house and he wasn't."
OL,26,@qD@KOUqD@WO]wD@JOUyD@aO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G7/13
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,448,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44708
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F447A1774037478
OL,3,CMurder trial told evidence points to
OL,4,C'some other killer'
OL,6,FThe barrister then discussed a former
OL,7,Fboyfriend of Ms McNally, who cannot be
OL,8,Fnamed due to a reporting restriction,
OL,9,Fbut who gave evidence during the trial.
OL,11,FMr Kearney said the former partner was
OL,12,Fthe "personification of reasonable
OL,13,Fdoubt" in this case.
OL,15,FHe said: "He is walking, talking
OL,16,Freasonable doubt."
OL,18,FHe said McCullagh had always believed
OL,19,Fthe ex-boyfriend was the killer.
OL,26,@tD@EOUuD@FO]wD@JOUxD@RO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G8/13
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,448,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44709
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F447A1774037478
OL,3,CMurder trial told evidence points to
OL,4,C'some other killer'
OL,6,FMr Kearney said the prosecution had
OL,7,Fclaimed McCullagh had accessed
OL,8,Fmessages on Ms McNally's phone but had
OL,9,Fnot identified any evidence about when
OL,10,Fthis happened.
OL,12,FThe barrister said the jury had heard
OL,13,Fevidence about hundreds of WhatsApp
OL,14,Fmessages exchanged between Ms McNally
OL,15,Fand McCullagh in the months before her
OL,16,Fdeath.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G9/13
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,448,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44710
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F447A1774037478
OL,3,CMurder trial told evidence points to
OL,4,C'some other killer'
OL,6,FHe said the messages showed the
OL,7,Frelationship was "continuing in the
OL,8,Fnormal way" and contrasted them with
OL,9,Fmessages she exchanged with her former
OL,10,Fpartner.
OL,12,FThe barrister said in 498 pages of
OL,13,Fmessages, there was "not a single
OL,14,Fcross word" between Ms McNally and the
OL,15,Fmurder accused.
OL,26,@oD@ROUpD@KO]uD@UOUvD@KO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}           G10/13
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,448,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44711
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F447A1774037478
OL,3,CMurder trial told evidence points to
OL,4,C'some other killer'
OL,6,FHe then turned to the prosecution
OL,7,Fcontention that McCullagh had given a
OL,8,F"false alibi" by stating he was taking
OL,9,Fpart in a livestream gaming session,
OL,10,Fwhen it had actually been recorded
OL,11,Fseveral days in advance.
OL,13,FThe barrister suggested there could a
OL,14,F"financial motive" to capturing
OL,15,Faudience interest by passing off
OL,16,Fonline events as live.
OL,18,FHe told the jury that the prosecution
OL,19,Fcase is "disintegrating in front of
OL,20,Fyou".
OL,26,@pD@AOUpD@MO]vD@AOUvD@RO]{D@IOU|D@DO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}           G11/13
